"Gerald Rudolph "Jerry" Ford, Jr. (born Leslie Lynch King, Jr. ; July 14, 1913 December 26, 2006) was the 38th President of the United States, serving from 1974 to 1977, and prior to this, was the 40th Vice President of the United States serving from 1973 to 1974. He was the first person appointed to the Vice Presidency under the terms of the 25th Amendment, after Spiro Agnew had resigned."@en
